        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "A proud educated man, first in his family to ever graduate high school, joined the State Dept. and got a great job at the French Embassy.  The year was 1903 and nothing could get better.  And it didn't.  Alfons walked into a street fight, two groups of students fighting by the canals in Paris.  He did not see the brick that laid him out, the next thing he knew he was in a cramped apartement with a handsome young student and it was late at night.  \"So you were drawn to our argument, our squabble, our cause.  Let me show you what it is all about.  My name is Lous.\"  And he fed him the blood and that was that. Alfons was a ghoul until the Nazi's came to Paris, his domitor embraced him, to better survive the run to the channel away from those Tremere bastards.  He has been serving the clan (and anyone else with a beef and money) battling the Tremere since.  Alfons never had a real goal or cause, hes a heartless mercenary poser, who has decided the money is in hating the tremere.  Hes a caricature of someone who has depth, he has none, and he is intensly afraid that someone will find out he is so fake."
        ],
